  "answer": "**Charles Comte's *Traité de la propriété: VOL I*, Chapter 13 (\"Influence du déboisement des montagnes sur les fleuves et les rivières.\")**[^1]\n\nComte cites Arthur Young's *Travels in France* (1787–1789) as eyewitness testimony to forest destruction in the Pyrenees, including men near Bagnères de Luchon \"cutting and splitting young birches, to make barrel hoops.\"[^2] The Lartigues passage, quoted below verbatim, laments the devastation:\n\n> This beautiful and noble forest of Lartigues has experienced a devastation so general, that it is almost entirely destroyed; there are no young shoots to replace the trees that have disappeared, and, in ten or twelve years, it will be nothing more than a bare mountain, with some miserable shrubs browsed by goats or by other animals.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Charles Comte, *Traité de la propriété: VOL I*, [Chapter 13](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-la-propriete-vol-i-2c7a99/13-influence-du-deboisement-des-montagnes-sur-les-fle/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Charles Comte, *Traité de la propriété: VOL I*, [paragraph](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-la-propriete-vol-i-2c7a99/13-influence-du-deboisement-des-montagnes-sur-les-fle/translation/#p-4ce3c5).\n\n[^3]: Charles Comte, *Traité de la propriété: VOL I*, [paragraph](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-la-propriete-vol-i-2c7a99/13-influence-du-deboisement-des-montagnes-sur-les-fle/translation/#p-5e30bb). (Quoting Arthur Young, *Travels during the years 1787, 1788 and 1789...*, vol. 2, p. 106.)",
